these  things  are  all  contributing  in  a  very  dynamic  way  to  a  huge  rise  in , especially  in  the  developing  world , in  people  's  interest  in  and  passion  for  democracy .
we  get  so  little  news  about  the  developing  world  that  we  often  forget  that  there  are  literally  millions  of  people  out  there  struggling  to  change  things  to  be  fairer , freer , more  democratic , less  corrupt .
and , you  know , we  do  n't  hear  those  stories  enough .
but  it  's  happening  all  over  the  place , and  these  tools  are  part  of  what  's  making  it  possible .
now  when  you  add  all  those  things  together , when  you  add  together  leapfrogging  and  new  kinds  of  tools , you  know , second  superpower  stuff , etc , what  do  you  get ? well , very  quickly , you  get  a  bright  green  future  for  the  developing  world .
you  get , for  example , green  power  spread  throughout  the  world .
you  get , this  is  a  building  in  hyderabad , india .
it  's  the  greenest  building  in  the  world .
