i  used  to  work  in  this  field  of  elementary  particles .
what  happens  to  matter  if  you  chop  it  up  very  fine ? what  is  it  made  of ? and  the  laws  of  these  particles  are  valid  throughout  the  universe , and  they  're  very  much  connected  with  the  history  of  the  universe .
we  know  a  lot  about  four  forces .
there  must  be  a  lot  more , but  those  are  at  very , very  small  distances , and  we  have  n't  really  interacted  with  them  very  much  yet .
the  main  thing  i  want  to  talk  about  is  this , that  we  have  this  remarkable  experience  in  this  field  of  fundamental  physics  that  beauty  is  a  very  successful  criterion  for  choosing  the  right  theory .
and  why  on  earth  could  that  be  so ? well , here  's  an  example  from  my  own  experience .
it  's  fairly  dramatic , actually , to  have  this  happen .
